value.value: This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in tendon, the fibrous bands or cords of connective tissue at the ends of muscle fibers that attach muscles to bones and other structures.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the ear, the sense organ in vertebrates that is specialized for the detection of sound, and the maintenance of balance.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the outer ear, part of the ear external to the tympanum (eardrum), consisting of a tube (the external auditory meatus) and the pinna (auricle).

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the mammary gland, the specialized exocrine gland of the skin of female mammals, which secretes milk for nourishment of the young.

This is any quantification of the physical form or structure of the largest veins (superior vena cava and inferior vena cava in mammals) which deliver de-oxygenated blood from throughout the body back to the right cardiac atrium.

This is any quantitation of the molecules, atoms and/or ions which constitute the chemical make-up of the largest veins (superior vena cava and inferior vena cava in mammals) which deliver de-oxygenated blood from throughout the body back to the right cardiac atrium.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the largest veins (superior vena cava and inferior vena cava in mammals) which deliver de-oxygenated blood from throughout the body back to the right cardiac atrium.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the cornea, the transparent anterior portion of the fibrous coat of the eye that serves as the chief refractory structure.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in great artery arising from the left ventricle from which the systemic arterial system proceeds.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in vibrissa follicles, the tubular invaginations of the epidermis enclosing the hair roots and from which grow the vibrissae (whiskers) located on the muzzle and face of many species.

label.value: heart right atrium ribonucleic acid level

value.value: This is a measurement of the amount of ribonucleic acid (RNA), the molecule composed of the sugar ribose, phosphate groups and any combination of the bases adenine, guanine, cytosine, and/or uracil, extracted from or contained in the heart right atrium, the upper chamber of the right side of the heart, which receives deoxygenated blood from the venae cavae and the coronary sinus, and pumps it into the right ventricle through the tricuspid valve.
This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in embryonic cells or tissue.
This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a one-cell embryo (zygote).
This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a two-cell embryo.
This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a four-cell embryo.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a blastocyst, a hollow ball of cells in an early-stage embryo containing two cell types, the inner cell mass and the trophectoderm.
This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a eight-cell embryo.
This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a female germ cell(s) that has entered meiosis.

label.value: inferior alveolar nerve ribonucleic acid level

value.value: This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) of which the tissue of the inferior alveolar nerve is formed or composed. The inferior alveolar nerve is the branch of the mandibular nerve responsible for sensory innervation to the gingivae of the lower jaw.

This is any quantitation of the molecules, atoms and/or ions which constitute the chemical make-up of a specified skeletal joint, one of the articulations between bones which may be immovable, slightly movable or freely movable.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the knee joint, the joint that joins the thigh with the leg and consists of two articulations: one between the femur and tibia, and one between the femur and patella.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in chondrocytes isolated from articular cartilage. Articular cartilage is a thin layer of cartilage, usually hyaline cartilage, on the articular surface of bones in synovial joints.

label.value: maximim inner diameter of middle cerebral artery perfused in bicarbonate-buffered, calcium-free saline

value.value: This is an ex vivo measurement of the length of a line which crosses a transverse view of a calcium-free physiological salt solution (PSS)-perfused (80 mmHg equilibrium pressure) middle cerebral artery, passing through its center and ending on either side at the inner surface of the blood vessel wall. The middle cerebral arteries are the largest of the cerebral arteries and supply blood to the lateral cerebral cortex, anterior temporal lobes and insular cortices of the brain.

label.value: resting inner diameter of middle cerebral artery perfused in bicarbonate-buffered, normal saline

value.value: This is an ex vivo measurement of the length of a line which crosses a transverse view of a saline-perfused (80 mmHg equilibrium pressure) middle cerebral artery, passing through its center and ending on either side at the inner surface of the blood vessel wall. The middle cerebral arteries are the largest of the cerebral arteries and supply blood to the lateral cerebral cortex, anterior temporal lobes and insular cortices of the brain.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a fracture hematoma, the first stage of healing for a bone fracture. The hematoma formation involves platelet aggregation, activation of the compliment cascade, and local hypoxia following the disruption of vasculature. The area is then invaded by a number of undifferentiated and committed cells resulting in the organisation of hematoma and the formation of granulation tissue.
This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a specified neoplastic tissue.

label.value: malignant, neoplastic tissue ribonucleic acid level

value.value: This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a specified malignant, neoplastic tissue.

label.value: benign, neoplastic tissue ribonucleic acid level

value.value: This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a specified benign, neoplastic tissue.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the endometrium, the glandular mucous membrane lining of the uterine cavity that is hormonally responsive during the estrous/menstrual cycle and during pregnancy.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a malignant tumor of the endometrium, the glandular mucous membrane lining of the uterine cavity that is hormonally responsive during the estrous/menstrual cycle and during pregnancy.

This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the mammary gland(s), a specialized accessory gland of the skin of mammals that secretes milk. The gland is typically only developed in females, and regresses in males.

label.value: mammary gland cancer ribonucleic acid level

value.value: This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in a malignant tumor of the mammary gland(s), a specialized accessory gland of the skin of mammals that secretes milk. The gland is typically only developed in females, and regresses in males.

This is a measurement which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation of the amount of inorganic pyrophosphate in a specified sample of plasma, the clear liquid that separates from blood after cells, platelets, and cellular debris has been removed.

label.value: total number of entries into the arms of an elevated plus maze

value.value: The count of movements of an experimental subject into any arm of an elevated plus maze, including entries into both open and enclosed arms.

label.value: number of entries into an enclosed arm of an elevated plus maze

value.value: The count of movements from the center of the elevated plus maze into either of the two arms of the maze that are enclosed by walls sufficiently high to prevent the escape of an experimental subject. The walls of the enclosed arms may be opaque to prevent the experimental subject from seeing anything outside the maze.

label.value: number of entries into an open arm of an elevated plus maze

value.value: The count of movements of an experimental subject into either of the two arms of an elevated plus maze that do not have walls to prevent the experimental subject from escaping or from seeing anything outside the maze.

label.value: amount of experiment time spent in a discrete space in an elevated plus maze

value.value: The total amount of time during an experiment that an organism or experimental subject spends in a distinct and specified area of an elevated plus maze (EPM). An EPM is an apparatus with an open center area, two open arms without enclosing walls and two enclosed arms with walls to prevent the experimental subject from escaping or from seeing anything outside the maze. The apparatus is raised a specified distance above the floor and is used to measure movement, behavior, learning, memory, etc., generally in rodents.

label.value: total amount of experiment time spent in an enclosed arm of an elevated plus maze

value.value: The cumulative amount of time during an experiment that an organism or experimental subject spends in either of the two arms of an elevated plus maze that are enclosed by opaque walls to prevent the experimental subject from escaping and from seeing anything outside the maze.

label.value: total amount of experiment time spent in any open area of an elevated plus maze

value.value: The cumulative amount of time during an experiment that an organism or experimental subject spends in any of the unenclosed areas of an elevated plus maze including the open center of the maze and/or the open arms of the maze.

label.value: total amount of experiment time spent in an open arm of an elevated plus maze

value.value: The cumulative amount of time during an experiment that an organism or experimental subject spends specifically in either of the two arms of the maze that do not have walls to prevent the experimental subject from seeing anything outside the maze.

label.value: number of 20 x 20 cm floor squares crossed into, out of, or within a discrete space in an open field apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the distance traveled in an open field apparatus, measured as a count of the squares of a 20 cm square grid marked on the floor of the apparatus, crossed by an experimental subject during an experiment. An open field apparatus is an arena, often but not always circular and brightly lit, enclosed in walls of sufficient height to prevent the escape of the experimental subject.

label.value: number of 20 x 20 cm floor squares crossed on the periphery of an open field apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the distance traveled within the region at the outer edge of an open field apparatus adjacent to the enclosing wall, measured as a count of the segments of a 20 cm square grid marked on the floor of the apparatus, crossed by an experimental subject during an experiment.

label.value: number of 20 x 20 cm floor squares crossed in the center of an open field apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the distance traveled within the open central region of an open field apparatus, measured as a count of the squares of a 20 cm square grid marked on the floor of the apparatus, crossed by an experimental subject during an experiment.
Measurement of the number of boli of fecal matter excreted within a specified period of time determined by counting the number of individual pellets deposited by the experimental subject.

label.value: number of lines crossed in the center of an open field apparatus

value.value: A measurement of the distance traveled within the region in the center of an open field apparatus, measured as a count of the grid lines, marked on the floor of the apparatus, crossed by an experimental subject during an experiment.

definition.value: This term should only be used when the measurement is "lines crossed" without information about the size or spacing of the lines or squares in the grid.

label.value: measurement of voluntary locomotion in an open field apparatus

value.value: Any measurement of the movement of an organism from one place to another in an open field apparatus when that movement originated and/or was undertaken, controlled, or accomplished as a result of free will or choice. An open field apparatus is an arena, often but not always circular and brightly lit, enclosed in walls of sufficient height to prevent the escape of the experimental subject.

label.value: measurement of voluntary locomotion in an elevated plus maze

value.value: Any measurement of the movement of an organism from one place to another in an elevated plus maze apparatus when that movement originated and/or was undertaken, controlled, or accomplished as a result of free will or choice. An elevated plus maze (EPM) is an apparatus with an open center area, two open arms without enclosing walls and two enclosed arms with walls to prevent the experimental subject from escaping or from seeing anything outside the maze. The apparatus is raised a specified distance above the floor and is used to measure movement, behavior, learning, memory, etc., generally in rodents.

label.value: number of entries into a discrete space in an elevated plus maze

value.value: A count of the number of times during an experiment that an organism or experimental subject moves into a distinct and specified area of an elevated plus maze (EPM). An EPM is an apparatus with an open center area, two open arms and two enclosed arms raised a specified distance above the floor. It is used to measure movement, behavior, learning, and memory, generally in rodents.

label.value: ratio of count of entries into an open arm of an elevated plus maze to total count of arm entries

value.value: The number of movements of an experimental subject into either of the two arms of an elevated plus maze that do not have walls to prevent the experimental subject from escaping or from seeing anything outside the maze divided by the total number of counts of the experimental subject entering any arm of the maze. Ratio may be expressed as a percentage.

label.value: medial collateral ligament ribonucleic acid level

value.value: This is any measurement of the absolute or relative amount(s) of one or more of the ribonucleic acids (RNAs) found in the medial collateral ligament, the tendon on the inner side of the knee joint that connects the femur and the tibia, thus helping to stabilize the joint.
